<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Google Says Criminal Hackers Used A.I. to Find a Major Software Flaw</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/google-hackers-attack-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/google-hackers-attack-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/google-hackers-attack-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The company said that it had identified, for the first time, hackers using artificial intelligence to discover an unknown bug. The attempted attack represents “a taste of what’s to come,” one expert said.</description><dc:creator>Dustin Volz</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 13:00:07 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Hacker (computer security)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/11/multimedia/11dc-cyber2-fqhz/11dc-cyber2-fqhz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Noah Berger/Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>“We have high confidence that the actor likely leveraged an A.I. model to support the discovery and weaponization of this vulnerability,” Google said in its report, published Monday.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>China Seeks A.I. Independence, Weakening Trump’s Leverage</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/12/business/china-semiconductor-ai-deepseek.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/12/business/china-semiconductor-ai-deepseek.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/12/business/china-semiconductor-ai-deepseek.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Before this week’s U.S.-Chinese summit, Beijing reached a milestone in its quest for technological self-sufficiency.</description><dc:creator>Meaghan Tobin</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 04:00:14 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer Chip</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">International trade</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">DeepSeek</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Huawei Technologies</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">NVIDIA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jen-Hsun Huang</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jensen Huang</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Xi Jinping</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/08/multimedia/00biz-china-chips-fqbm/00biz-china-chips-fqbm-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Kelsey McClellan for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>DeepSeek said for the first time that its new model had been optimized to run on chips made by the Chinese tech giant Huawei.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>